From: Grant Metson
Sent: Monday, August 11, 2025 8:42 AM
To: Raffaella del Prete <raffaellanz@icloud.com>
Cc: Stephen Walker <swalker@asurnz.com>; Sasha Cotterill <Sasha.Cotterill@t=
ower.co.nz>; Chris Cornwall <Chris.Cornwall@tower.co.nz>
Subject: 23 Mays Road, Devonport - C90306048 - Repair Scoping - 12:30 today

Good morning Rafaella,
As per the next phase of the process map - Stephen Walker from ASURNZ - our=
 Technical Building Consultant is due to visit site and author the scope of=
 works required.
Stephen and I will be visiting site at 12:30 today to complete the walk-thr=
ough and determine the scope-of-works for the repairs to your home.
Once we have completed this document - I can return and go through each ite=
m on the scope line-by-line in detail with you so you can gain the confiden=
ce that we have captured everything.
When we go through the scope together - we can consider adding anything fur=
ther that is necessary if we need to. I am exceptionally confident that Ste=
phen and I will capture everything on the first draft - but I want you to k=
now that you will sign-off on the scope-of-works as being complete before w=
e move to the repair phase.
You do not need to join us for today's visit - but you are more than welcom=
e to if you wish. As I stated - we can review it together once complete. I =
will let you decide whether you wish to join us or not.
Please do not hesitate to contact me if you have any questions or concerns =
at all.
Many Thanks,
Grant.

[cid:image001.png@01DC0AD9.D96D9250]
Grant Metson
Regional Manager - House Assessing
Phone 021 744 288
Level 5, 136 Fanshawe Street,
PO Box 90347, Auckland 1142

